{
  "stem": "5103.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there were carrots and things that I used to eat raw, with-- without the skin even peeled, you know?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was a story even in the other place which I forgot to tell you, where I used to take the carrots out of the rabbit's cage-- because my father used to do it.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because they used to feed the rabbit for Christmas so that we'd have a nice Christmas dinner.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But-- and so there were carrots going in there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father used to steal them out and give them to me so I could eat them in the nighttime, and I have some kind of nourishment before I went to sleep.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And from there, we had to leave, and we were allocated a place in Haarlem, in the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] It was a very narrow street, like a lane, and we were told to go there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Mom, and Dad, and myself, we went there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't know how we risked it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My mother looked very thin, and my father had false papers.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "His name was Johannes Peter Bink, and I think my mother must have had some papers as well, but she was his wife, supposedly, so she must've been Bink as well.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we arrived in this [INAUDIBLE], and we knocked on the door and a lady opened the door.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And if you imagine-- you can see it here, terrace houses in Paddington-- a terrace house, with a long, long corridor, long corridor.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at the end of the corridor, bright lights, like as though-- now, we've been darkness.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There's been no lights, electric light.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Always everything was blackened and all, you know?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Holland was in darkness.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "All of a sudden, you come into, you walk in, and she said, Come in!",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
